name: La discepola del santone - Cancro vietnamita

deck: A reprint of two 1974 Argentine comic stories featuring Killing. The reprint has been translated into English.
description:
SADISTIK The King of Crime! is reprint that also provides an English translation of Killing comics. Originally printed in 1974 in the Argentine comic magazine Skorpio, the stories differ from the Italia Killing in that they are drawn rather than photo comics, and depict Killing as more of a vigilante/crime fighter than a criminal. The translation was done by Mort Todd and released in March of 2015.

CONTENTS

I AM DEATH! Once upon a time a man put on a skeleton suit and began an incredible career in crime! But who was he and how did he meet his companion Dana? This tale from Argentina purports to tell it all!

ART OF AN ASSASSIN! Additional art work from Ernesto García as well as some information about the Argentinean paperback series.

THE DEATH OF SADISTIK! Meet the mysterious, masked crime fighter SKORPIO! A dying French man wants a priest to find the vigilante… How does this all connect to the end of the Monster with a 1000 Masks?

Note

Killing is the name used for both the original Italian series and the character. Kiling was the character name used in the Argentine series but because the character is referred to as Sadistik in English, the translator has opted for the English Name.
